# Generated catch-all: exports every top-level object whose name doesn't start
# with a dot. Replace with roxygen-generated NAMESPACE (via `devtools::document()`)
# once @export tags are added per-function. Until then this keeps every helper
# accessible after `library(seekit)`.
exportPattern("^[^.]")

# Imports. The de-CATALYST plotters used to borrow CATALYST's namespace (the
# `environment(...) <- asNamespace('CATALYST')` hack) to resolve bare calls like
# gpar()/rowAnnotation()/geom_density_ridges(). With CATALYST removed, winglab
# imports these itself so bare external calls resolve in the package namespace.
